The last [[execution]] of a civilian carried out in [[Albania]] was a [[hanging]] on 29 June 1995. While capital punishment was abolished for murder on 1 October 2000, it was still retained for treason and military offences. The reason for the abolition of the death penalty in Albania as well as in other European nations is the signing of Protocol No. 6 to the [[ECHR]]. In Albania this came into force on 1 October 2000.

Albania under communism the death penalty was used highly from 1941-1985.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lajme.shqiperia.com/lajme/artikull/iden/367106/titulli/Varja-e-Havzi-Neles-PD-zbardh-vendimin-dhe-firmen-e-Kristaq-Rames|title=Varja e Havzi Nelës, PD zbardh vendimin dhe firmën e Kristaq Ramës|accessdate=14 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.klosi.org/news/klosi_news_oponion/154.html|title=KLOSI – Poeti disident Havzi Nela...|work=Klosi News|access-date=2017-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007045122/http://www.klosi.org/news/klosi_news_oponion/154.html#|archive-date=2014-10-07|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

In 2007 Albania ratified Protocol No. 13 to the ECHR, abolishing the death penalty under all circumstances, replacing it with [[life imprisonment in Albania|life imprisonment]].



