{{BLP sources|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox politician | honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles|Yang Berbahagia Tan Sri]] | name = Chong Hon Nyan | occupation = Politician | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1924|6|21|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Federated Malay States]], [[British Malaya]] | module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes | s = 张汉源 | t = 張漢源 | p = Zhāng Hànyuán | h = Chong1 Hon4-ngien2}} }} [[Malay titles|Tan Sri]] '''Chong Hon Nyan''' ({{lang|zh|张汉源}}; born 21 June 1924, [[Kuala Lumpur]]) is a [[Malaysia]]n politician of Chinese descent.
He is the former [[Ministry of Health (Malaysia)|Minister of Health]] and [[Ministry of Transport (Malaysia)|Minister of Transport]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Hon Nyan defends changes to Nurses Act |newspaper=[[New Straits Times]] |date=29 April 1980 |page=8 |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1309&dat=19800429&id=DJJUAAAAIBAJ&sjid=948DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6552,5444919&hl=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Hon Nyan: We've other strategies |newspaper=New Straits Times |date=2 August 1984 |page=7 |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1309&dat=19840802&id=28kpAAAAIBAJ&sjid=pY4DAAAAIBAJ&pg=7088,396508&hl=en}}</ref>
