{{Infobox organization |name = Saudi Society of Dermatology and Dermatologic Surgery |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = SSDDS |motto = |formation = 1989 |extinction = |type = Scientific Society (non-profit) |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]] |region_served = [[Saudi]] |membership = |language = |leader_title = President |leader_name = [[Dr. Omar Abdul Aziz Al-Sheikh]]<ref name="SSDDS_pres">[http://www.winteracademy.net/downdoc.php?id_doc=57&lng=1&rif=c5649d8217 Winter Academy Newsletter], Congress St., Moritz and Pontresina, April 2–5, 2009: Page 7.</ref> |main_organ = [[Dermatology|Skin]] and its [[Skin Diseases|Diseases]] |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.ssdds.org/ena/index.php?option=com_frontpage&Itemid=22 www.ssdds.org] |remarks = }}
The '''Saudi Society of Dermatology and Dermatologic Surgery''' (in [[Arabic]] '''الجمعية السعودية لأمراض وجراحة الجلد'''), commonly abbreviated as SSDDS, (formerly '''The Saudi Society of Dermatology and Venereology'''), is a scientific organization that was established in 1989; to unite [[dermatologist]] and [[venereologist]] in [[Saudi Arabia]] to contribute their experiences and research for the development of healthcare [[solution]]s to skin diseases facing the citizenry in the country and other dermatologic related issues.
Dr. Sami Al Sogair has been attributed to the foundation of the [[society]], who also stands as its president since 1989 until 1994.
In 1994, an SSDDS election installed Dr. Omar Abdul Aziz Al-Sheikh as president and holds this post up to present.{{Citation needed|date=October 2010}}
==Activities== The 13th National Symposium of the SSDDS was held on 30–31 December 2009.<ref name="Conf1">[http://www.ssddsconferences.org/index.php?option=com_frontpage&Itemid=1 13th National SSDDS Conference] Website accessed on 2 November 2010.</ref>
