{{Infobox university | name = Shaheed Syed Nazrul Islam Medical College | native_name = শহীদ সৈয়দ নজরুল ইসলাম মেডিকেল কলেজ | native_name_lang = bn | image = Shahid Syed Nazrul Islam Medical College logo.png | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = Logo of Shahid Syed Nazrul Islam Medical College | other_name = <!-- or: | other_names = --> | former_name = <!-- or: | former_names = --> | established = {{start date|2011}} | type = [[Public university|Public]] [[medical school]] | academic_affiliation = [[University of Dhaka]] | principal = [[Prof. Dr. Mansur Khalil]] | director = | academic_staff = 20 | administrative_staff = | students = 260 | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Kishoreganj]] | state = | country = [[Bangladesh]] | coor = {{Coord|24.7617|N|90.3993|E|region:BD_type:edu|display=inline,title}} | campus = [[Urban area|Urban]]<ref>{{cite news|title=কিশোরগঞ্জে শহীদ সৈয়দ নজরুল ইসলাম মেডিকেল কলেজের জমি হস্তান্তর|url=http://www.dailybnbnews.com/old/18505#.VFZRZvmUc5k|accessdate=2014-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=সৈয়দ নজরুল মেডিকেল কলেজের ভূমি বুঝে পেল কর্তৃপক্ষ|url=http://archive.prothom-alo.com/detail/date/2013-02-11/news/328391|publisher=[[Prothom Alo]]|accessdate=2014-11-03}}</ref> | language = [[English language|English]] | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | footnotes = }} '''Shahid Syed Nazrul Islam Medical College''' ({{lang-bn|শহীদ সৈয়দ নজরুল ইসলাম মেডিকেল কলেজ}}) is a [[Public university|government]] [[medical school]] in [[Bangladesh]], established in 2011. It is located at [[Kishoreganj District|Kishoreganj]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Shahid Syed Nazrul Islam Medical College|url=http://app.dghs.gov.bd/orgregistry/org_profile.php?org_code=10002296|work=Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MoHFW)|accessdate=2014-11-02}}</ref> The college is affiliated with [[University of Dhaka]] as a constituent college.<ref>{{cite web|title=University of Dhaka - OFFICE OF THE INSPECTOR OF COLLEGES|url=http://www.du.ac.bd/list_of_colleges.php|work=Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MoHFW)|accessdate=2014-11-02|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150830085809/http://www.du.ac.bd/list_of_colleges.php|archivedate=2015-08-30|df=}}</ref>
It offers 5 years [[MBBS]] degree programme and admits 52 students every year.
==History== Shahid Syed Nazrul Islam Medical College was established in 2011. It was named after [[Syed Nazrul Islam]], the first acting [[President of Bangladesh]].
In the year 2010-2011, Bangladesh government approved to establish 4 medical colleges at [[Jessore]], [[Satkhira]], [[Kishoreganj]] and [[Kushtia]] with a view to improve the healthcare services in the country. Executive Committee of the National Economic Council ([[ECNEC]]) endorsed the project. An estimated cost of Tk 5.45 billion was approved as budget to establish Shahid Syed Nazrul Islam Medical College.<ref>{{cite news|title=ECNEC approves 8 projects worth Tk 23.23 billion|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/old/more.php?page=detail_news&date=2012-07-25&news_id=137904|publisher=[[The Financial Express (Bangladesh)]]accessdate=2014-11-03}}</ref> The project included construction of six storied hospital building, five storied college for academic building, nurses training center, students hostel, internee doctors' hostel, doctors' dormitory, staff nurses' dormitory, mosque, auditorium, principal and directors' residential buildings, installation of gymnasium, procurement of equipment, one micro-bus, two ambulances and furniture with the fund.
